5-6 medium size large Tomatoes
1 tbsp grated cheese (mozzarella, asiago, parmesean, jalsberg)
Salt, pepper to taste. 
Brown Rice (cooked)
1 tbsp grated cheese 
Jar tomato sause

Preheat  oven

Wash the tomatoes (or peppers) and set dry.

Cut the top of tomato (or pepper) like a cap. Gently scoop out the centers . Keep aside the scooped portion and chop the cut tops in bowl mix rice with small amount of tomato sauce and season.

Fill tomatoes (or peppers) with the mixture.

Top with grated cheese.

Place tomatoes in a glass baking dish

Cook for 25-30 minutes at 350F.
